        <bioghist id="ref2">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Carlton W. Werkau served as the Secretary-Treasurer for the Communications Workers of America (CWA) from 1943 until his death in 1955.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>This collection consists of photographs, both personal and union related, correspondence, and CWA records. The CWA records consist of Convention proceedings from 1953-1955 as well as a strike manual and tax files. Articles and letters concerning Werkau's death in 1955 are also included.</p>
        </scopecontent>
